ENGLISH VERSION (EN)  
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. GRANT OF LICENSE  
The author hereby grants a restricted, non-exclusive, non-transferable license for the use of this software exclusively within the internal scope of the University of São Paulo (USP), including authorized technical staff, faculty members, researchers, scholarship holders, interns and administrative collaborators.

2. PERMISSIONS  
The following uses are allowed without the need for further authorization:  
a) execution of the software;  
b) reuse of the code for institutional purposes within USP;  
c) internal adaptation of the code for processing future editions of the USP Statistical Yearbook;  
d) internal redistribution among USP units or administrative sectors, provided that this license and the author’s identification remain intact.

3. RESTRICTIONS  
The following actions are strictly prohibited unless expressly authorized in writing by the author:  
a) modifying, altering, adapting or creating derivative works for use outside USP;  
b) redistributing, publishing, disclosing or making the software available to third parties not institutionally affiliated with USP;  
c) using the software for any commercial purpose, whether direct or indirect;  
d) sublicensing, selling, leasing or otherwise commercially exploiting the software.

4. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY  
All intellectual property rights, including source code, documentation and software structure, remain solely with the author, in accordance with Brazilian Copyright Law (Law 9.610/98) and applicable international norms.

5. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY  
The software is provided “as is”, without any explicit or implied warranties, including but not limited to warranties of fitness for a particular purpose.  
The author shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, administrative or other damages arising from the use, interpretation or inability to use this software.

6. ACCEPTANCE  
By using this software, the user acknowledges that they have read, understood and fully agreed to the terms of this license.

